# User Management API

The User Management API provides endpoints for managing users, authentication,
and user profiles. This API follows REST principles and returns JSON responses.

## Authentication

All API requests require authentication using an API key or OAuth 2.0 token.
Include the `Authorization` header in all requests.

# Group Users

Resources related to user management.

## Users Collection [/users]

### List All Users [GET]

Retrieve a paginated list of all users.

+ Parameters
    + page: `1` (number, optional) - Page number
    + limit: `20` (number, optional) - Items per page

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
                "id": "user-1",
                "email": "user1@example.com",
                "name": "John Doe",
                "role": "user",
                "createdAt": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
            },
            {
                "id": "user-2",
                "email": "user2@example.com",
                "name": "Jane Smith",
                "role": "admin",
                "createdAt": "2024-01-10T08:00:00Z"
            }
        ]

### Create a User [POST]

Create a new user account.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "email": "newuser@example.com",
            "name": "New User",
            "password": "securepassword123",
            "role": "user"
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "id": "user-3",
            "email": "newuser@example.com",
            "name": "New User",
            "role": "user",
            "createdAt": "2024-01-20T14:00:00Z"
        }

+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "error": "validation_error",
            "message": "Email already exists"
        }

## User [/users/{userId}]

+ Parameters
    + userId: `user-1` (string, required) - The user's unique identifier

### Get User [GET]

Retrieve a specific user by their ID.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "id": "user-1",
            "email": "user1@example.com",
            "name": "John Doe",
            "role": "user",
            "createdAt": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z",
            "profile": {
                "avatar": "https://example.com/avatars/user1.png",
                "bio": "Software developer",
                "location": "San Francisco, CA"
            }
        }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
            "error": "not_found",
            "message": "User not found"
        }

### Update User [PUT]

Update an existing user's information.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "name": "John Updated",
            "role": "admin"
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "id": "user-1",
            "email": "user1@example.com",
            "name": "John Updated",
            "role": "admin",
            "createdAt": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
        }

### Delete User [DELETE]

Delete a user account.

+ Response 204

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
            "error": "not_found",
            "message": "User not found"
        }

# Group Authentication

Resources for user authentication.

## Login [/auth/login]

### Authenticate User [POST]

Authenticate a user and receive an access token.

+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "email": "user@example.com",
            "password": "password123"
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "access_token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...",
            "token_type": "Bearer",
            "expires_in": 3600,
            "refresh_token": "dGhpcyBpcyBhIHJlZnJlc2g..."
        }

+ Response 401 (application/json)

        {
            "error": "authentication_failed",
            "message": "Invalid email or password"
        }

## Logout [/auth/logout]

### Logout User [POST]

Invalidate the current access token.

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...

+ Response 204

# Data Structures

## User (object)
+ id: `user-1` (string, required) - Unique identifier
+ email: `user@example.com` (string, required) - Email address
+ name: `John Doe` (string, required) - Full name
+ role: `user` (string) - User role (admin, user, guest)
+ createdAt: `2024-01-15T10:30:00Z` (string) - Creation timestamp

## UserProfile (object)
+ avatar: `https://example.com/avatar.png` (string) - Avatar URL
+ bio: `Software developer` (string) - Biography
+ location: `San Francisco, CA` (string) - Location

## Error (object)
+ error: `validation_error` (string, required) - Error code
+ message: `Validation failed` (string, required) - Error message
